@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<section>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [6/20/2025]</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>JournalApp (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our web application.</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> We do not require you to provide personal information such as your name, email, or address to use JournalApp.</li>
        <li><strong>Journal Entries:</strong> Any journal entries or content you create within the app are stored locally on your device’s database and are not transmitted or shared externally.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Your journal entries are stored locally using SQLite on your device. We do not collect, store, or share your journal content on any servers or third parties. The app does not track or monitor your usage.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>Since your data is stored locally, it remains under your control. However, we recommend you back up your data regularly. We use industry-standard security practices within the app but cannot guarantee complete security due to factors beyond our control.</p>

    <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>JournalApp does not use cookies or tracking technologies.</p>

    <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>JournalApp does not use third-party analytics or advertising services.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Choices</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You can delete your journal entries at any time within the app.</li>
        <li>Since data is stored locally, uninstalling the app or deleting the database file will remove all your data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We encourage you to review it periodically.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:<br />
        Email: RK7-0R@protonmail.com<br /></p>
</section>
